            <strong>🇸🇩 At least 200 killed in paramilitary attack in Sudan</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Sudanese paramilitary forces and the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-02-2025-br1-4-killed-over-400-people?source=website" target="_blank">killed over 400 people</a>, including infants, in a three-day assault on villages near al-Gitaina, White Nile state, according to a rights group. The RSF reportedly executed civilians, abducted individuals, and looted homes, with some victims drowning while fleeing.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This attack comes as Sudan’s army makes gains against the RSF in Khartoum. Meanwhile, the RSF and allied factions delayed announcing a rival government to the one recently formed for broader representation. The conflict, which began in April 2023, has killed many and displaced over 12 Mn.</p>
        </mj-text>
