            <strong>🇧🇷 Brazillian prosecutor charges Bolsonaro with 2022 coup plot</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro has been formally <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-02-2025-br2-5-charged-with-attempting-a-coup?source=website" target="_blank">charged with attempting a coup</a> and allegedly signing on a plot to poison President Lula da Silva. Prosecutor-General Paulo Gonet says Bolsonaro and 33 accomplices orchestrated a Green and Yellow Dagger plan to undermine democracy and prevent Lula from taking office after the 2022 election.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The conspiracy allegedly involved attacks on the electronic voting system, voter suppression, and inciting the violent January 8, 2023, riots. Prosecutors also uncovered a plan to assassinate VP Geraldo Alckmin and Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes. Bolsonaro has denied the charges and says he is being politically persecuted. The Supreme Court will decide whether to proceed with a case against him.</p>
        </mj-text>
