          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Why was South Sudan separated from the mainland?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/south-sudan-secession-youngest-nation.png" alt="South Sudan seceded from the mainland and became the youngest nation" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">South Sudan seceded from the mainland and became the youngest nation. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;"><a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-02-2025-f1-6-south-sudan-separated-from-sudan?source=website" target="_blank">South Sudan separated from Sudan</a> primarily due to long-standing ethnic, religious, and political conflicts. This division was the result of decades of civil war between the predominantly Arab and Muslim north and the mainly Christian and animist south. On July 9, 2011, South Sudan seceded from Sudan and became the world’s newest nation. 
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Sudanese government in Khartoum engaged in several brutal wars against southern rebel groups, primarily the Sudan People's Liberation Army (SPLA), over issues of autonomy and resources. The Comprehensive Peace Agreement in 2005 ended the second civil war, granting South Sudan autonomy and the right to hold a referendum on independence.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">In a 2011 referendum, over 98% of South Sudanese voted for independence, leading to the official separation. Despite gaining independence, South Sudan has faced ongoing internal conflicts and economic struggles. The young nation faces challenges such as illiteracy, poor health care, lack of infrastructure, human rights abuses by the southern military, and the development of oil resources.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
